## Objective

Lock the cluster-level design decisions for landing UP Framework v5.1.3 on AKS, before Part 01 (Architecture & Maturity) goes to draft. We leave the meeting with **twelve locked decisions**, **three escalation lists** with named owners, and a **pre-filled Day 0 / 1 / 2 RACI**.

## In scope

- Cluster topology and environment separation
- Networking, identity, RBAC, and tooling stack
- Pipeline and deployment identity
- Policy & cyber gates — Bank Azure Policy initiative, CIS AKS Benchmark, admission
- Day 0 / Day 1 / Day 2 ownership

## Out of scope (today)

Chart-by-chart UP-FW deployment, operator install order, detailed NetworkPolicy YAML, capacity model, cost model, DR drill plan.

